310 g Chicken Breast Tenders
1 unit Mini Cucumber
2 unit Tomato
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
16 g Mediterranean Spice Blend
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
56 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Ciabatta Roll
4 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium-high (approx. 500°F). Wash and dry all produce.
Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise, then into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Halve ciabatta roll, then brush each half with 1/2 tbsp oil. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine yogurt sauce, half the feta and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) oil. Stir to combine. Set aside.

Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
To a medium bowl, add chicken, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, salt, pepper and Mediterranean Spice Blend.
Toss to coat.

Add chicken to the grill. Close lid and grill for 5-6 min, flipping occasionally, until cooked through.**
Arrange ciabatta halves on the other side of the grill. Grill on 2-3 min per side, until warmed through and grill marks form. (TIP: Keep an eye on ciabatta so they don't burn!)

Thinly slice chicken.
Tear grilled ciabatta halves into crouton-sized pieces.
To the large bowl with yogurt-feta dressing, add spinach, cucumbers and tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.
Divide salad between plates. Top with chicken, ciabatta croutons and remaining feta.